        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(agents): reuse media tool availability during tool prep",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Reuse the optional media tool factory plan for image, video, and music generation tool registration.\n- Let media generation tool factories skip duplicate registration-time availability scans when `createOpenClawTools` already resolved availability.\n- Preserve latest main behavior for async media task yielding and explicit-workspace image provider planning.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Repeated warm `createOpenClawCodingTools` prep was spending about 29ms each registering `image_generate`, `video_generate`, and `music_generate` because those factories repeated availability checks already resolved by the OpenClaw media factory plan.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, branch `media-tool-availability-pr4c`; original warm in-process tool prep probe after one warmup call, plus current-head regression verification after rebasing onto `origin/main` at `4dad7bd93b`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a local `node`/`tsx` probe that imports `createOpenClawCodingTools`, records `recordToolPrepStage` timings, discards one warmup call, then records 30 warm samples; after the latest rebase, ran the focused media-tool regression suite, core test typecheck, formatter check, `git diff --check`, and `pnpm build` on current head `e242dccc50`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\noriginal warm prep probe after fix:\ntotal p50 103.68ms, p95 110.16ms\nopenclaw-tools:image_generate registration p50 0.005ms\nopenclaw-tools:video_generate registration p50 0.002ms\nopenclaw-tools:music_generate registration p50 0.002ms\n/usr/bin/time -l max RSS 850575360 bytes\n\ncurrent-head regression verification:\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.agents-tools.config.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.media-factory-plan.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.test.ts --reporter=dot\n4 test files passed, 178 tests passed\n\n./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/openclaw-tools.media-factory-plan.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.media-factory-plan.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.ts src/agents/tools/image-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.ts src/agents/tools/video-generate-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.ts src/agents/tools/music-generate-tool.test.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/core-test.tsbuildinfo\nexit 0\n\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\nexit 0\n\npnpm build\nexit 0; phase timings total 140.7s, slowest tsdown 91.0s\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Single-call warm p50 improved by about 84ms versus the same-probe baseline, from 187.74ms p50 to 103.68ms p50. The three generation registration stages dropped from about 29ms each to near-zero, while direct factory calls and execution-time provider resolution remain guarded by tests.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full end-to-end paid provider media generation was not run; this PR changes registration-time availability reuse and preserves execution-time provider resolution paths.\n",
